Hi,

I got an error when using the built-in Method signature refactoring with
Object... as parameter. To reproduce, create a class as:

public class Test {
	public void foo(Object... p) {
	}
	
	public void bar() {
		foo();
	}
}

Then go on the function declaration of "foo", press Alt-Shift-C (or whatever
refactoring method sigs is) and remove the parameter p.

BOOM.


Here's the log I get that way.

Hope it helps.. keep on the good work. Eclipse is best! ;-)
